{"id": "1514628744822657215", "channel_id": "1514628744822657215", "type": 0, "author_id": "959661546408124416", "author_name": "sui.yu.er.an", "author_bot": false, "content": "忘記他叫什麼了\n什麼時候能換抽抽了<:Aurita_please:1356053110375714817>", "timestamp": "2026-06-11T13:53:53.207000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1514628745221247128", "filename": "Screenshot_2026-06-11-21-47-57-666_com.sialiagames.z1.gp.twnew.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 112284, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1514628744822657215/1514628745221247128/Screenshot_2026-06-11-21-47-57-666_com.sialiagames.z1.gp.twnew.jpg?ex=6a2c0f71&is=6a2abdf1&hm=4a92672aabe5ab1106e2f77d562e8fce126146066d235a0ff5a0e7bf1750624e&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1514628744822657215", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "薔薇......什麼的", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168103141416960"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1514623679491735562", "channel_id": "1514623679491735562", "type": 0, "author_id": "756481426739822642", "author_name": "paseoli", "author_bot": false, "content": "currently, the event awakener/WoD banners in the game indicate that we only have basically a 1/3 (33.33%) chance of obtaining a RATE UP character. I find this mechanic to be deeply disruptive of an otherwise really good game for the following reasons:\n\n1. Some if not most awakeners' potential are locked behind enlightenment levels. ergo, a player needs multiple copies of some characters to maximize them. while this mechanic basically exists in all of gacha, it is admittedly more frustrating in morimens specifically because of the abysmally low chance of getting a  RATE UP character (again only 33.33%). \n\n2. the word rate up on this pulling event is simply misleading. is it really appropriate to call it a RATE UP when statistically speaking a player is almost twice as likely to get a random character rather than the rate up character? that is 66.66% to get a random character and for the RATE UP a good old 33.33%. it just doesnt make sense to put the words RATE UP when given the probabilities. not to mention the game requires us to lose 2 times before being guaranteed to the character/WoD we want. there is a non-zero chance for the gacha to take 90 pulls for a player to get the supposed rate up character. thrice the amount the pity for an ssr character (w/c is 30 pulls).\n\ntldr, the gacha aspect of this game is frustrating to deal with. here are some suggestions:\n1. make the weighted probability for rate up characters/WoDs at least >= 50%. 33.33% for a supposed rate up character/WoD is just way too small.\n2. make it so a player only needs to lose once to guarantee the next ssr they pull is the rate up awakener/WoD\nEither one of the two being implimented is already a big step forward. But honestly implimenting both would be really nice. That is all and thank you for taking time to read through all this.", "timestamp": "2026-06-11T13:33:45.538000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1514623679491735562", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Rework event character/WoD gacha mechanic", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1514626643119964271", "channel_id": "1514623679491735562", "type": 0, "author_id": "756481426739822642", "author_name": "paseoli", "author_bot": false, "content": "correction: there is a 50% chance to get the rate up WoD however the probability for awakers are indeed 33.33% \ni made a mistake there for the WoD probability", "timestamp": "2026-06-11T13:45:32.122000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1514623679491735562", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Rework event character/WoD gacha mechanic", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
